ere is a pattern of\nreciting called jatha, ratha, ghanapatha etc which if you observe closely is\nnothing but a  memorizing technique. The culture of writing was not\nencouraged. So the question of British and Moghuls destroying the\nVeda-Shaakhaas does not arise.\n\nWhat can be understood is that, the number of Gurukulas and Brahmacharis\nwishing to memorize Vedas were reducing day by day, with the advent of The\nAge of Kali, and as such various Shaakhaas or disciplines got extinct as\nnone were left to either render or memorize them. Whatever written version\nof Vedas you see now is may be due to a few people who have memorized it has\npenned it down. However, Vedas are Shrutis(that which is heard) and not\nSmritis(that which is written or remembered). So it does not make any point\nto &quot;read&quot; a &quot;written&quot; Veda. Guru-upadesha or upanishata is always heard in\nright hear, and never read or written.\n\nAs Vedas are very vast each Shaakha has its Rishi as head and a separate\ndepartment. This was for ease of administration. Obviously as different\nRishis come into picture, each Shaakha gets slightly modified to suit the\ninclination of the Rishi. The Vedas were like open ended source code or\nWikipedia, where each Rishi can upgrade or modify it at relevant points\nbased on his tapasya and realizations. This gives a different taste to\nShaakha. However, the core fundamentals remains the same. So there is\nnothing really worrisome that we have lost Shaakhas, as in my opinion, they\nwere incorporated for administrative ease. If you can master even one\nShaakha well, it is enough.\n\nThese are my opinions and one must not accept it until and unless it\nconvinces one&#39;s intellect, and when I give opinion, I may be wrong. Only\nShri Brahmarishi Gurudeva is blemishless and knows best. Thank You.\n\nWith Kind Regards,\nKannan\n____________________________________________________________________________\n__________________________________________________