ze Vedas were reducing day by day, with the advent o=\r\nf The Age\nof Kali, and as such various Shaakhaas or disciplines got extinct=\r\n as none were\nleft to either render or memorize them. Whatever written vers=\r\nion of Vedas you\nsee now is may be due to a few people who have memorized i=\r\nt has penned it down.\nHowever, Vedas are Shrutis(that which is heard) and n=\r\not Smritis(that which is\nwritten or remembered). So it does not make any po=\r\nint to &#8220;read&#8221; a &#8220;written&#8221;\nVeda. Guru-upadesha or up=\r\nanishata is always heard in right hear, and never read\nor written.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;=\r\n\nAs Vedas are very vast each Shaakha has its Rishi as head and a separate d=\r\nepartment.\nThis was for ease of administration. Obviously as different Rish=\r\nis come into\npicture, each Shaakha gets slightly modified to suit the incli=\r\nnation of the\nRishi. The Vedas were like open ended source code or Wikipedi=\r\na, where each\nRishi can upgrade or modify it at relevant points based on hi=\r\ns tapasya and\nrealizations. This gives a different taste to Shaakha. Howeve=\r\nr, the core\nfundamentals remains the same. So there is nothing really worri=\r\nsome that we\nhave lost Shaakhas, as in my opinion, they were incorporated f=\r\nor administrative\nease. If you can master even one Shaakha well, it is enou=\r\ngh.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nThese are my opinions and one must not accept it until and unl=\r\ness it convinces\none&#8217;s intellect, and when I give opinion, I may be w=\r\nrong. Only Shri Brahmarishi\nGurudeva is blemishless and knows best. Thank Y=\r\nou.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nWith Kind Regards,&lt;br&gt;\nKannan&lt;br&gt;\n____________________________=\r\n___________________________________________________________________________=\r\n____________________________________________&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;f=\r\nont-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Palatino Linotype&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;&#39;&gt;